headline: Walt Disney’s CEO Roller Coaster: Why Josh D’Amaro Can Smooth the Ride
summary: Bob Iger succeeded at Disney in the golden age of cable. His successor, a theme park veteran, struggled from cable’s decline, Covid, and the rise of streaming. Now the stock is relatively cheap, and Splash Mountain has taken over the income statement and the company.
